messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /api/products/{id}/reviews

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false

- POST: true

- OPTIONS: false

- TRACE: false

- GET: false

- PUT: false

- DELETE: false

- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- In server.js the product routes are mounted with app.use('/api/products', productRoutes), so every route defined in routes/productRoutes.js is prefixed with /api/products.
- In routes/productRoutes.js the route that leads to the createProductReview controller is defined as router.route('/:id/reviews').post(protect, checkObjectId, createProductReview); which combines with the mount path to produce /api/products/:id/reviews. Per your formatting requirement, that becomes /api/products/{id}/reviews.
- Only POST is registered on that route in the code, so POST is the only acceptable method.
- No GET (and therefore no automatic HEAD handling by a GET route) is defined for this path, and there is no explicit handling for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, or PATCH in the provided router, so those methods are not acceptable per the code.
